Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "upaliti" in different forms and positions, with the starred word highlighted and translations provided in parentheses:

1. *Upalio* sam svetlo u sobi. (I turned on the light in the room.)
2. Da li si ti *upalila* grejanje? (Did you turn on the heating?)
3. Molim te da mi *upališ* muziku. (Please turn on the music for me.)
4. *Upalili* smo vatru da se zagrejemo. (We lit a fire to warm ourselves up.)
5. Nikada ne bih *upalio* cigaretu u zatvorenom prostoru. (I would never light a cigarette in an enclosed space.)
6. Kada *upališ* mašinu, budi pažljiv. (When you turn on the machine, be careful.)
7. Moramo *upaliti* motore i krenuti. (We have to start the engines and go.)
8. Već pola sata pokušavam da *upalim* ovaj kompjuter. (I've been trying to turn on this computer for half an hour already.)
9. *Upali* mi svetlo kada dođeš kući. (Turn on the light for me when you come home.)
10. Ko je *upalio* ovu sveću? (Who lit this candle?)

I hope these examples are helpful!